This paper deals with the chase procedure, which is a fundamental algorithmic tool in database theory. Therefore, it is most likely to belong to the cs.DB (Databases) sub-category. The paper also involves formal logic and decision problems, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) sub-category. The use of TGDs and the focus on termination also suggest that the paper could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves algorithmic analysis and complexity, which could place it in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves decidability, which could also place it in the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category.
